  "texts": [
    "Canny Edge Detection Canny edge detection is a classic computer vision technique used for detecting edges in images.",
    "It was introduced by John Canny in 1986 and remains widely used due to its effectiveness.",
    "The Canny edge detection algorithm involves multiple steps, including noise reduction, gradient calculation, non-maximum suppression, and thresholding.",
    "It aims to identify significant changes in intensity, which correspond to edges in the image.",
    "Canny edge detection is useful for tasks such as image segmentation, object recognition, and feature extraction."
  ],
